<item>
            <title>[HIVE-14294] HiveSchemaConverter for Parquet doesn&apos;t translate TINYINT and SMALLINT into proper Parquet types</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-14294</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;To reproduce this issue, run the following DDL:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-sql&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;CREATE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;TABLE&lt;/span&gt; foo STORED &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/span&gt; PARQUET &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;CAST&lt;/span&gt;(1 &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;TINYINT&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And then check the schema of the written Parquet file:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;$ parquet-schema $WAREHOUSE_PATH/foo/000000_0
message hive_schema {
  optional int32 _c0;
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When translating Hive types into Parquet types, &lt;tt&gt;TINYINT&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;SMALLINT&lt;/tt&gt; should be translated into the &lt;tt&gt;int32 (INT_8)&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;int32 (INT_16)&lt;/tt&gt; respectively. However, &lt;tt&gt;HiveSchemaConverter&lt;/tt&gt; converts all of &lt;tt&gt;TINYINT&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;SMALLINT&lt;/tt&gt;, and &lt;tt&gt;INT&lt;/tt&gt; into Parquet &lt;tt&gt;int32&lt;/tt&gt;. This causes problem when accessing Parquet files generated by Hive in other systems since type information gets wrong.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
